Being content in the moment doesn\'92t mean forgetting about the future entirely.  How do you balance your present pleasures with your journey toward living a more virtuous life? \
\
Sunbaking is a nice pleasure in nature but if you indulged all day your future health, and goals would suffer. If you are fully appreciating the pleasure with all your attention in the moment then you can savour it quickly without over indulging. Find that sweet spot then apply your attention to the next virtuous goal until \ul that\ulnone  sweet spot is reached or interrupted by life obstacles or opportunities. Veer back on to the path of goals with the natural flow of circumstance. 
