\
Contentment can\'92t be achieved unless we stop comparing ourselves to others but it can be hard to do. How can you gain control of this emotion? \
\
Coveting is imagining the pleasure they must feel from what they have, the attention they must get, the opportunities, the adoration, the benefits which implies that you are a victim because you miss out on those hard to get things that comes easily to them It is a sign that not enough attention has been paid to the root cause of the success the effort that can be learned from by pivoting envy to curiosity. This will keep thoughts realistic in both the sacrifice and benefits and how that applies to you path while appreciating what pleasure you can take from being happy for them. Breaking down the virtues they employed to achieve what they have is the \ul real\ulnone  gift of \ul their\ulnone  success.\
\
\
What do you need to be happy and content? \
\
The right mindset, focused on virtues:\
Courage - Take action\
Justice - Do the right thing\
Temperance - Do it consistently\
Wisdom - Calculated with resources available\
\
\
\
How can you free yourself from the expectations of others so that you can live a life that is virtuous and dutiful, but free?\
\
Freedom is finding \'93belief\'94 (which is especially difficult for someone who has only ever believed in \'93people\'94 some of which let me down) that there is no good or bad in nature just true or false everything else is just my or their perspective of things which cannot be trusted. Act not on the perceptions but on the true/false that is the root cause contributing to their perception. You will exceed their expectations and yours. Be flexible enough to revise your true/false assumptions with new data specific to the exact moment nature is presenting you at the time. Nothing is ever locked in, it is all a starting point to relate to when applying it to suit that instant.\
\
\
Examine what you do \'93for show\'94 or to impress others. What would happen if you let go of this desire to impress and focused instead on what you need to make yourself happy? How would things be different?\
\
My desire to \'91impress\'92 has come from cars and rockstar fantasy not typically from clothes or appearance but from respect or adoration appreciation for my art or resourcefulness. The car thing has been about best bang-for-buck not modicifation expression (showing off resourcefulness) rather from expression of wealth. Rockstar thing is more about ideas that are presented creatively with humour, or wordplay/poetry/musically and the undeniable connection that has made with an audience. Both are an fantasy motivation and has been an outlet for creative or ingenuity callings that I realised need to be motivated for my own benefit not for the fantasy. Appreciation from others will neither motivate nor discourage me.\
\
