What do you have now that you once craved in the past? How can you learn to be satisfied with it instead of constantly wanting more? \
\
Love. Respect. Validation. Letting go of getting the exact amount of those things in the exact way at the exact time because it never happens and I don\'92t need it. When attentive in the moment, acting on virtuous motivation instead keep ambition internal and realistic instead of external and unrealistic which burns endless energy which ignores other things. Letting go of the need for \'93proof of love\'94 or respect is embracing that i don\'92t need or am motivated by those external things that are out of my control and if internally motivated when do come they won\'92t mean anything. But if they are taken away then that won\'92t mean anything either.\
\
\
Instead of always trying to acquire more and different things, how can you change your mindset so that what you have now is exactly enough? \
\
I will need to revisit some of what I have to make full use of and be content with what remains. Music is best when what sounds are their have been very calculated and curated to be a mix of noise and gaps between of equal value, and too much is a cluttered mix instead of being sparsely composed to appreciate every nuance. Things and pleasures are the same, they need to be culled down to small morsels of savoury and shareable treats. This will minimise waste and feed/be appreciated by the most, including myself. Instead of the search for more, the attention to resourcefulness of what is present is what will bring contentment.\
